JOHANNESBURG - An attempt by the ANC in Johannesburg to have mayor Herman Mashaba removed through a motion of no confidence received a knock on Thursday night when the council voted to keep Mashaba and Vasco da Gama.  EFF leader Julius Malema had tweeted to former mayor and ANC councillor Parks Tau that he would never by Joburg mayor again.  Earlier in the day, the EFF also helped the DA's Nelson Mandela Bay mayor Athol Trollip keep his position.  eNCA